We have to work together to streamline permits so we can create more clean energy jobs.

For Nevadans recovering from fentanyl and other drug addictions, access to telehealth services is essential.

That's why my colleagues and I have introduced the TREATS Act, to maintain access to telehealth services and continue to expand care for all Nevadans.

My legislative, press, and in-state interns are doing an incredible job every day helping me advocate for Nevada. If you're interested in an internship with my office in Spring 2024, please apply by Nov. 15.

This week's jobs report is great news for Nevada families, but I'm not stopping here.

We have more to do to create more opportunities for Nevadans and lower costs, and I'm going to keep working in the Senate with 
@SenateDems
 to lead that fight for our working families.

It's simple: birth control should be available over the counter, with no out-of-pocket cost or a prescription.

Now that the 
@US_FDA
 has approved the first OTC birth control in the country, I'm pushing to make sure women can afford it.

On this day in 1968, Shirley Chisholm became the first African American woman ever elected to Congress. She fought hard her entire career to overcome discrimination and blazed a trail for future generations to follow. I'm proud to celebrate her incredible legacy today.

Addiction therapy through telehealth is already helping Nevadans in rural communities recover from drugs like fentanyl and other opiates. This works.

Now, I'm working to maintain access so more Nevadans can get the addiction care they need.

When my grandmother was diagnosed with Alzheimer's, my whole family rallied to care for her. It's personal to me.

So this #AlzheimersAwarenessMonth, I'm proud to join families and advocates all across the country to fight for the investments in treatment and research they need.

Senate Republicans’ harmful proposal isn’t a serious effort to secure the border — it would make things worse, not better.

I helped introduce a bipartisan bill with

I'm standing in solidarity with the men and women of Local 525 who are pushing for the fair wages and benefits that they have earned.
